Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new reasoning protocol and embeds it into the multi-agent reinforcement learning framework, which falls under the domain of AI. 
2. cs.GT (Game Theory) - The paper discusses the convergence of the GR2 learners to at least one Nash Equilibrium, which is a concept in game theory. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses the Soft Actor-Critic algorithm, which is a machine learning algorithm, to evaluate the GR2 methods. 
4. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper focuses on multi-agent reinforcement learning and proposes a new reasoning protocol for such systems. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the bounded rationality of agents in the GR2 model, which is a concept in control theory.
